06/09/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan met with Albanian counterpart Sali Berisha in Ankara on Tuesday (5 September), assuring him that Turkey would continue to assist Albania in implementing requirements for entry into the Alliance.
Erdogan also offered assistance in the restructuring of Albania's police sector.
They also discussed ways for enhancement of the bilateral economic and trade ties.
Next week, Berisha makes his first formal visit to Athens.
(Albanian News - 06/09/06)
